	<!-- Introduction -->
	<purpose>
		<p>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of the assignment of classification information to product or activity data.
	</p>
	<p>   
		The second edition of this part of ISO 10303 included the modifications to the first edition listed below.
	</p>
	
	<p>
		The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been modified:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Classification_attribute.</li>
		</ul>	
		<p>
		The following MIM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been added:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>classification_identification_item;</li>
			<li>classification_classification_item;</li>
			<li>classification_role in USE FROM list from management_resources_schema.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
		The following MIM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been renamed:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>id_for_class renamed to cwa_identification_item;</li>
			<li>version_for_class renamed to cwa_versionable_item.</li>
		</ul>
		
		<p>
		Modifications made to the mapping specification of the following entity definitions:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Classification_assignment.items - added;</li>
			<li>Class_hierarchy.super_class and Class_hierarchy.sub_class - removed;</li>
			<li>Classification_attribute - changed;</li>
			<li>Classification_attribute.allowed_values and Classification_attribute.characterized_class - fixed syntax errors.</li>
		</ul>

